{
  "doc_id": "19276",
  "text": "Inflammatory Breast Cancer (IBC) is a rare but aggressive form of breast cancer that is diagnosed clinically [CITATION_1] . IBC has characteristic clinical and biologic features suggestive of differences between IBC and non-IBC. Egypt has about a five times higher proportion of IBC patients than the USA (2-4) with distinct molecular features of IBC tumors that may reflect a more aggressive nature of the disease [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Within Egypt, there have been no past comparisons between IBC and non-IBC patients with respect to survival. Therefore, as a part of this study, we decided to compare survival of IBC and non-IBC patients while taking into account, the epidemiologic, pathologic, and treatment characteristics of these two groups of patients from the National Cancer Institute of Cairo University (NCI-Cairo) in Egypt.",
